Description:
The Opportunity

We're the creator of BetterSleep: the app that has helped more than 65 million people sleep and feel better across the globe. We have a sleep tracker, relaxing sounds, guided meditations and sleep stories, all available in over 6 different languages! We set out on a mission to help people change their lives with a better night's sleep.

Who are we and why should you join us?

We are taking sleep to the next level. We combine quality content, cutting edge technology, and data-driven product development to constantly learn, iterate, and improve.
We are relentless in our pursuit of excellence, always challenging the status quo and discovering new ways of doing things with the goal of always serving our users better.
We are a community that grows together - both professionally and personally. Our team is agile, allowing each employee to make a real impact from day one.
We invest in the well-being and professional development of our team, because we recognize that business growth and individual growth go hand in hand. You will grow quickly and be challenged every day. Join us!

What are we looking for?

Your mission as a data scientist will be to join our data team and undertake analysis, dashboarding, and data modeling along with supporting data engineering projects.

Responsibilities

As part of the data team, you'll collaborate with the rest of your team to help with daily tasks;
Collaborating with the dev team on data collection and data quality validation;
Using statistical methods to analyze experiments (A/B tests) data or other data and generate useful business reports;
Building Dashboards, running Ad hoc analysis, and providing insightful reports to help teams with the decision-making process;
Building data pipeline components and ELTs/ETLs;
Working closely with the User Acquisition team, Product team, CRM team, and Content team to evaluate the performance of new features and strategies for teams;
Research and Implement Machine Learning initiatives in collaboration with the engineering and data teams.

Requirements

Degree in mathematics, statistics background, or any other relevant field;
Experience with data visualization and dashboard building;
Experience with product analytics platforms is a plus (MixPanel, Amplitude, etc.);
Experience with Machine Learning;
Experience with SQL (BigQuery is a plus) and Python.

Benefits

Competitive salary & compensation;
Excellent health, dental, and vision coverage;
Retirement plan with employer matching contribution;
Ridiculous perks program;
Office in the heart of downtown Montreal, a three-minute walk from the Central Station;
50% discount on public transport and monthly meal allowance (Uber eats);
Free access to Tele-health & BetterHelp services;
Any hardware/software that will make you productive and successful;
Awesome people to work with;
Nothing to slow you down;
Helping people live a better life, every day.

At BetterSleep we thrive on difference and individuality, and as part of the Teladoc Health family, we are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We never have and never will discriminate against any job candidate or employee due to age, race, ethnicity, religion, sex, color, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, medical condition, marital status, parental status, disability, or Veteran status.

